Your Honor,

I stand before you today, pleading guilty to the offense of shoplifting a dress worth approximately 2000 pounds. I want to take this opportunity to express my deep remorse and regret for my actions.

I am 18 years old, a first-time offender, and I aspire to pursue a career in nursing after high school. I understand the seriousness of the offense and I am committed to taking responsibility for my actions.

I acknowledge that it was wrong to shoplift the dress, and I fully understand the value of respecting other people's property. My intention is to learn from this mistake and ensure that I do not repeat such actions in the future.

I humbly request your leniency, Your Honor, considering my young age, lack of criminal history, and my sincere commitment to making amends. I am determined to demonstrate my remorse by adhering to the rules and regulations of society and working towards becoming a responsible member of the community.

Thank you for considering my plea, Your Honor. I assure you that I will strive to learn from my mistakes and prove myself as a law-abiding citizen.

Respectfully,
Melissa Cox
